  <steps>
    <step num="0">Preheat oven to 400°F (200˚C). </step>
    <step num="1">Slice the jalapeños in half, then remove the seeds by scraping out the insides. </step>
    <step num="2">Spread the cream cheese evenly among the jalapeño shells. </step>
    <step num="3">Wrap each jalapeño in bacon. </step>
    <step num="4">Place the bacon-wrapped jalapeños on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake for 20 minutes, until bacon is browned and peppers are tender. </step>
